5.

A data modeler is designing a MongoDB-based system for an online retail platform. The product catalog's schema has evolved over time, with new attributes being added and existing ones being modified.

To maintain backward compatibility and support efficient queries across multiple versions of product documents, what schema versioning strategy should the data modeler implement?

(Choose 1)

Correct Answer

a.
Keep all versions of a product document in separate collections, such as products_v1, products_v2, and create a new collection for each schema iteration.
b.
Add a version field to each product document, and increment this field whenever a schema change occurs.
c.
Implement a polymorphic schema where each product document is allowed to have a unique structure without a specific versioning field.
d.
Use foreign key references between documents of different schema versions and maintain a master document to track the version of each user document.

=> B


